---
const company = {
  name: "Sonberg Consulting AB",
  app: "Supply Guard",
  email: "supply-guard@sonberg-consulting.se"
};
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <title>Privacy Policy | {company.app}</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 2rem auto;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: #222;
        padding: 0 1rem;
      }
      h1,
      h2 {
        color: #111;
      }
      h1 {
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
        font-size: 2rem;
      }
      h2 {
        margin-top: 1.5rem;
        font-size: 1.3rem;
      }
      a {
        color: #0070f3;
      }
      .logo {
        width: 200px;
        margin-left: -0.5rem;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <img src="/supply-guard-long.png" class="logo" alt="Supply guard logo" />
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: 9/11 2025</em></p>

    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy describes how {company.name} (“we”, “our”, or “us”) collects,
      uses, and discloses information when you install or use the
      {company.app} app (“the App”) in connection with your Shopify store. We are
      committed to protecting your privacy and handling your information securely
      and lawfully. For any questions, contact us at
      <a href={`mailto:${company.email}`}>{company.email}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
    <h3>a. From Merchants</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Store name domain</li>
      <li>Shopify store ID and access tokens</li>
      <li>Inventory and product data needed for stock monitoring</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How We Use the Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>To provide and operate the {company.app} app</li>
      <li>To analyze stock and forecast inventory</li>
      <li>To offer technical support and improve functionality</li>
      <li>To comply with Shopify and legal requirements</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Sharing of Information</h2>
    <p>We do not sell or rent any data. Information is shared only:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>With Shopify, as required for functionality</li>
      <li>
        With service providers (e.g., Microsoft Azure) under data-processing
        agreements
      </li>
      <li>As required by law</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>
      We retain data for as long as your subscription remains active. When you
      uninstall the app, data is deleted within 30 days unless legally required
      otherwise. You may also request deletion via
      <a href={`mailto:${company.email}`}>{company.email}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
    <p>
      Depending on your location, you may request access, correction, or
      deletion of your data, or object to processing. Requests can be sent to
      <a href={`mailto:${company.email}`}>{company.email}</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
    <p>
      We use encryption (HTTPS/TLS), secure storage, and access controls on
      Microsoft Azure (EU region). While no system is completely secure, we
      continuously improve our safeguards.
    </p>

    <h2>8. International Data Transfers</h2>
    <p>
      Data is processed and stored in the European Union. If transferred outside
      the EU, we rely on approved Standard Contractual Clauses.
    </p>

    <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>
      We may update this Privacy Policy occasionally. Continued use of the App
      after updates indicates acceptance of the new terms.
    </p>

    <h2>10. Contact Information</h2>
    <p>
      {company.name}<br />
      Email: <a href={`mailto:${company.email}`}>{company.email}</a><br />
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
